               <birth notBefore="1847" notAfter="1850">He was born at 
                  <placeName ref="LOC6242WarraH"/> between<date>1847–1850</date>.</birth>
               <floruit notBefore="1870" notAfter="1916">He was an important ruler of <placeName ref="LOC6185Wallo"/> and 
                  the entire northern Ethiopia. 
                  He was born Muslim and later converted to Christianity after the council of <placeName ref="LOC1980BoruMe"/> in <date>1878</date> and assumed the baptismal name Mikaʾel. 
                  He maintained an alliance with <persName ref="PRS10378Yohanne"/> until the emperor’s death in <date>1889</date> at the battle of 
                  <placeName ref="LOC4637Matamm"/>. 
                  After <persName ref="PRS10378Yohanne">Yoḥannǝs’s</persName> death
                  he declared his submission to <persName ref="PRS7006Menilek"/>
                  to whom he was loyal till the end of his reign. He was one of the military commanders at the 
                  battle of <placeName ref="LOC1263Adwa"/>
               </floruit>
               <death when="1916">He was killed at the battle of <placeName ref="LOC5446Sagale"/> in <date>1916</date>. </death>
